# Email Utility Module

This module provides functions to send emails with optional HTML formatting and attachments using Python's built-in smtplib and email libraries. It is designed for internal use within the WCAP environment.

## Overview

This module is instantiated using the `MailServer` class. It requires the vault's internet API key and the credential ID for the SMTP2GO entry in the vault (see Mitch for details). Credentials are fetched from an `InternetCredentialManager` at construction time.

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Test Email",
           "This is a plain text email.")
```

The module includes:

- A core method `send_email()` for sending emails with flexible options.
- A convenience wrapper `email_reporting()` for sending plain-text notifications to the internal Reporting distribution list.

## Classes

### MailServer

#### Signature

```
MailServer(internet_password_key: str, smtp2go_credential_id: int)
```

#### Description

Construct a `MailServer` instance wired to SMTP2GO. Credentials are pulled from an `InternetCredentialManager` initialised with `internet_password_key`; the SMTP username and password are looked up by `smtp2go_credential_id`.

Outbound mail is sent via `mail.smtp2go.com` on port `587` using `STARTTLS`.

#### Parameters

- `internet_password_key` (str): The vault API key used to initialise an `InternetCredentialManager`.
- `smtp2go_credential_id` (int): The vault entry ID for the SMTP2GO credential.

## Methods

### send_email()

#### Signature

```
send_email(
    sender: str,
    recipients: list[str] | str,
    subject: str,
    body: str,
    body_type: str = "plain",
    attachments: list[Path | tuple[str, bytes]] | None = None,
    cc: list[str] | str | None = None,
    bcc: list[str] | str | None = None,
) -> None
```

#### Description

Sends an email with optional HTML body, attachments, and CC / BCC recipients.

#### Parameters

- `sender` (str): Email address of the sender. Must be in the approved-senders list: `python@wcap.ca`, `workflow@wcap.ca`, `reports@wcap.ca`. Any other sender raises `ValueError`.
- `recipients` (list[str] | str): A single recipient address or a list of addresses.
- `subject` (str): Subject line of the email.
- `body` (str): Email body text (plain text or HTML depending on `body_type`).
- `body_type` (str): `"plain"` (default) or `"html"`.
- `attachments` (list[Path | tuple[str, bytes]] | None): Optional list of attachments. Each item is either a `pathlib.Path` pointing to an existing file (read from disk) or a `(filename, raw_bytes)` tuple (attached in-memory).
- `cc` (list[str] | str | None): Optional carbon-copy recipients — same shape as `recipients`.
- `bcc` (list[str] | str | None): Optional blind carbon-copy recipients — same shape as `recipients`.

#### Raises

- `ValueError`: If `sender` is not in the approved-senders list, or any address (sender, recipient, cc, or bcc) fails the `EMAIL_PATTERN` format check.
- `FileNotFoundError`: If a `Path` attachment does not exist on disk.
- `TypeError`: If an attachment item is neither a `Path` nor a `(str, bytes)` tuple.

#### Behavior

- Validates `sender` against the approved-senders list.
- Normalises `recipients`, `cc`, and `bcc` into lists and validates each address.
- Builds a `MIMEMultipart` message and attaches body as plain text or HTML.
- Adds attachments (from disk `Path` or in-memory `(filename, bytes)` tuple).
- Sends via `mail.smtp2go.com:587` with `STARTTLS`, authenticating using the SMTP2GO credentials fetched from the vault.

### email_reporting()

#### Signature

```
email_reporting(subject: str, body: str) -> None
```

#### Description

Shortcut for sending a plain-text email to the internal Reporting distribution list.

#### Parameters

- `subject` (str): Email subject.
- `body` (str): Plain-text email body.

#### Behavior

- Uses `send_email()` internally.
- Sender: `python@wcap.ca`
- Recipient: `Reporting@wcap.ca`

## Usage Examples

### Send a plain text email

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Test Email",
           "This is a plain text email.")
```

### Send an HTML email

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "HTML Email",
           "<h1>Hello</h1><p>This is an HTML email.</p>",
           body_type="html")
```

### Send with CC and BCC

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Team Update",
           "Heads up, team.",
           cc=["manager@wcap.ca"],
           bcc="audit@wcap.ca")
```

### Send with a file attachment from disk

```
from pathlib import Path

mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Report",
           "Please find the attached report.",
           attachments=[Path("report.pdf"), Path("data.csv")])
```

### Send with an in-memory attachment

Pass a `(filename, bytes)` tuple to attach data that lives only in memory (e.g. a dataframe rendered as CSV bytes, a generated PDF, etc.).

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)

csv_bytes = df.to_csv(index=False).encode("utf-8")

mail_server.send_email("python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Daily Extract",
           "Attached is today's extract.",
           attachments=[("daily_extract.csv", csv_bytes)])
```

### Send a reporting email
```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Credential-ID>)
mail_server.email_reporting("Reporting report", "This is a log message")
```
